7.32	Exercise_urticaria	Exercise urticaria	Exercise urticaria is a form of urticaria (skin rash) that happens during or after exercise, e.g. jogging or running. Urticaria is an allergic reaction in the skin characterized by itching -- as well as possible rash, swelling or hives -- on the legs, arms, torso or neck. Exercise urticaria is also referred to as exercise allergy, itchy legs, itchy legs syndrome or runners itch.	
